Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.35,0:00:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome,\Nbrothers and sisters, to JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.02,0:00:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In this month’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.19,0:00:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll learn ways to deal with worry and anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.76,0:00:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some highlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.86,0:00:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,From childhood, this brother found it a challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.97,0:00:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to attend meetings, go to school, hold a job,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.60,0:00:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and even leave his home each morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.87,0:00:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we learn from his experience
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.88,0:00:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to help us cope with our anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.98,0:00:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one day at a time?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.41,0:00:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,These two sisters have worked\Nshoulder to shoulder in full-time service
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.85,0:00:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for more than 60 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.15,0:00:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll learn what has helped them to remain joyful
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.72,0:00:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,despite everyday struggles and unexpected trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.06,0:00:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever wondered what motivates
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.06,0:00:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters\Nto make themselves available for Bethel service?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.47,0:00:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll hear from ones who are serving at Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.67,0:00:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll learn how to prepare and qualify
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.81,0:01:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for this special form of full-time service.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.31,0:01:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s much to enjoy in this May 2019 edition
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.22,0:01:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you sometimes feel completely overwhelmed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.81,0:01:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,when life’s problems cause you anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.68,0:01:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just trying to provide the necessities
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.48,0:01:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for one’s family can lead to anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.38,0:01:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.38,0:01:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you might be dealing\Nwith a chronic or life-threatening illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.42,0:01:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,caring for a sick or elderly relative,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.56,0:01:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,grieving the death of a loved one,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.59,0:01:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,loneliness, a natural disaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.90,0:01:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe you’re struggling\Nwith the devastating effects
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.90,0:02:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of past or present abuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.27,0:02:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you firmly believe\Nthat God’s Kingdom will fix these problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.94,0:02:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but that’s in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.18,0:02:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What about today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.28,0:02:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you feel like David,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who prayed at Psalm 13:2:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.05,0:02:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“How long will I have anxious concern,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.19,0:02:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with grief in my heart each day?”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.19,0:02:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A sister who has struggled\Nwith anxiety for many years wrote this:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Anxiety robs me of sleep,\N impacts my health,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.27,0:02:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,affects the way I treat others,\Nand makes me want to give up.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.28,0:02:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,She added: “Anxiety is like a monster
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“that lives in my body\Nsomewhere between my heart and my belly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.72,0:02:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“I cannot wait for Jehovah\Nto kill that monster in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.99,0:02:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“But until then,\Nthe monster snarls and tears at my insides
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.16,0:03:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and tries to take over my life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.73,0:03:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you identify with her feelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.47,0:03:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We often hear a person say concerning anxiety:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.97,0:03:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’m just trying to take it one day at a time.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But one brother put it this way:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.98,0:03:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“I try to take it one day at a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.68,0:03:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but sometimes several days attack me at once.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.42,0:03:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,For so many of us, anxiety is a daily struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you battle with anxiety,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.90,0:03:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,please know this: You are not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.93,0:03:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not give up the fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.97,0:03:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah and Jesus are aware of the anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.94,0:03:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that weigh on your mind\Nand that are deep in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.88,0:03:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body\Nknows that living in this system of things
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.41,0:03:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is especially “hard to deal with.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the theme chosen for this program is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.39,0:04:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Deal With Anxiety One Day at a Time.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.39,0:04:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,First, what is anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Christian Greek Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.83,0:04:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the word “anxious” occurs 19 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The first occurrence\Nis in Jesus’ Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.27,0:04:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jesus knew that people\Nworried about how to provide for their family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.94,0:04:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So at Matthew 6:25,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.95,0:04:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,he gave this wise counsel:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.78,0:04:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“On this account I say to you:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.55,0:04:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“Stop being anxious about your lives
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.16,0:04:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“as to what you will eat or what you will drink,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.53,0:04:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“or about your bodies as to what you will wear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.66,0:04:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Does not life mean more than food
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the body than clothing?”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.77,0:04:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Study Bible note for verse 25
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.41,0:04:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,says that “the Greek term for ‘anxious’
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“can refer to worry that divides a person’s mind
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:04:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and distracts him, robbing him of joy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.95,0:05:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At Luke 12:29,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.05,0:05:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus says to “stop being in anxious suspense”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.56,0:05:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or to “stop worrying.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.96,0:05:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The study note here says
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.23,0:05:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Greek word\Nfor “anxious suspense” was used
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.90,0:05:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to refer “to ships being tossed at sea.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.00,0:05:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It says that Jesus used it “figuratively
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.74,0:05:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“for being anxious or unsettled,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.51,0:05:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“as if tossed about or wavering
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.31,0:05:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,because of doubt and anxiety.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.41,0:05:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,By saying “stop being anxious,”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus recognizes\Nthat anxiety is already in progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.65,0:05:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He is very aware of our imperfect nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.49,0:05:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that we tend\Nto bring our worries from yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.33,0:05:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,(the would-haves,\Ncould-haves, and should-haves)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.97,0:05:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and our imagined worries about tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,(the what-ifs) to today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.74,0:05:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But ask yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.74,0:06:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How often have I worried myself\Nsick about what might happen tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.48,0:06:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,only to find that tomorrow\Nwasn’t nearly as bad as I feared it would be?’
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.82,0:06:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus also knows that anxiety can have real,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.42,0:06:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes painful, consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.56,0:06:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It can stop us from making spiritual progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.43,0:06:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Overthinking and overanalyzing our problems
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,can literally shut us down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.50,0:06:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How, though, can we “stop being anxious”?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.04,0:06:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the antidote?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.48,0:06:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider four practical things we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.21,0:06:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,First, rely on Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.98,0:06:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and take one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.79,0:06:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is exactly what Jesus prescribed for us
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 6:33, 34:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.23,0:06:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep on, then, seeking first the Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.63,0:06:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“and his righteousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.63,0:07:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“and all these other things will be added to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“So never be anxious about the next day,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.81,0:07:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“for the next day will have its own anxieties.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Each day has enough of its own troubles.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 34 has a study note
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.35,0:07:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,telling us that “undue anxiety\Nabout what may happen in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.02,0:07:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“can adversely affect\Na person’s relationship with God,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.59,0:07:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,causing him to rely \Non his own wisdom rather than on God’s.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what’s the lesson?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.10,0:07:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of relying on ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.70,0:07:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,rely on Jehovah, and take one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.44,0:07:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A cross-reference to Matthew 6:34
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,takes us to Exodus 16:4.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.08,0:07:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In this account,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.42,0:07:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah provided\Nthe Israelites with enough manna
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.05,0:07:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for every day of their 40-year trek.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.76,0:07:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Could Jehovah have provided
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.93,0:08:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a week’s worth of manna?\Na month’s worth? a year’s worth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.73,0:08:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.73,0:08:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So why did\Nhe only provide enough for each day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.00,0:08:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When they stepped out\Nof their tents each morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.01,0:08:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no question whether\Nthere would be manna on the ground or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.01,0:08:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was\Nno question where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah never failed to provide for their needs,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.76,0:08:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,not even for one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.92,0:08:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They also knew from the past that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.76,0:08:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,always provided for those who were loyal to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.83,0:08:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We too can look back\Nat how Jehovah provided for his servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.50,0:08:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We can have\Ncomplete confidence that Jehovah knows exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.81,0:08:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what we need when we need it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.61,0:08:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,—for today, tomorrow, and for all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.61,0:08:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we have such confidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.45,0:08:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,why do we sometimes continue to feel anxious?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.15,0:09:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The simple answer:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.32,0:09:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re imperfect people trying our best
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve Jehovah in Satan’s wicked world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.56,0:09:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Daily challenges cause anxiety\Nthat can make us forget to rely on Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and take one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.90,0:09:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to add\Nour second way to deal with anxiety:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.57,0:09:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Pour your heart out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah in earnest prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.71,0:09:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Read with me the reassuring words
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.82,0:09:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,at Philippians 4:6, 7:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.29,0:09:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be anxious over anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.79,0:09:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“but in everything by prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.79,0:09:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“and supplication along with thanksgiving,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.23,0:09:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“let your petitions be made known to God;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.40,0:09:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the peace of God that surpasses
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.74,0:09:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“all understanding will guard your hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.80,0:09:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and your mental powers by means of Christ Jesus.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.94,0:09:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul doesn’t simply tell us not to be anxious,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.68,0:09:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but he tells us how.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.98,0:10:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He said “by prayer and supplication,”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.15,0:10:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which is earnest and specific prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,With what benefit?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.99,0:10:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The “peace of God . . . will guard your hearts.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Guard” was a military expression referring to troops
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.73,0:10:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,assigned to protect a city.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.90,0:10:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The inhabitants could sleep soundly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.84,0:10:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that soldiers were guarding them at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.71,0:10:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In a similar way,\Nwhen we have “the peace of God,”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.81,0:10:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,our hearts and minds can rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.68,0:10:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This can prevent us from being\Noverwhelmed by anxiety or discouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.69,0:10:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How reassuring are the words of the psalmist
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.39,0:10:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at Psalm 4:8:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.70,0:10:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will lie down and sleep in peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.73,0:10:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“for you alone, O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.97,0:10:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,make me dwell in security.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.94,0:10:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we feel trapped,\Nlike there’s no way out of our worries,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.94,0:11:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the peace from God gives us hope
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.58,0:11:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that there’s light at the end of the tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What, though, must you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn your worries into deep, heartfelt prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.52,0:11:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, at 1 Peter 5:7,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.36,0:11:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah invites you\Nto “throw all your anxiety on him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.03,0:11:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“[and leave it with him]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.13,0:11:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because he cares for you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is the one person\Nwho truly understands how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.31,0:11:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows every moment of your life
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.41,0:11:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—why you feel or react a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.75,0:11:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He loves and values you personally
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.42,0:11:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,despite your imperfections, your anxieties,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.19,0:11:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your cares and worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.66,0:11:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He not only has\Nthe power to help you, he wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.80,0:11:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing this\Nshould move you to pray specifically,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.14,0:12:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,expressing your deepest emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.20,0:12:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and pleading\Nthat he grant you peace of mind and heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.21,0:12:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,To the extent you do so,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.65,0:12:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Peter 5:10 promises
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.15,0:12:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that “he will make you firm,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.82,0:12:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“he will make you strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.89,0:12:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,he will firmly ground you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.49,0:12:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Never underestimate the power of prayer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is always ready to help you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.20,0:12:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.27,0:12:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Our third way to deal with anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.70,0:12:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is to read and meditate on God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.51,0:12:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let Jehovah speak to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.54,0:12:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow Jehovah’s thoughts to become your thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At Psalm 94:19,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.49,0:12:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how the psalmist admitted his own anxiety:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.32,0:12:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“When anxieties overwhelmed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.66,0:13:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you comforted and soothed me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.13,0:13:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, even servants of God\Ncan feel overwhelmed by anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or, as one translation says,\N“burdened with worries.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.44,0:13:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That in itself is comforting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.14,0:13:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that an inspired Bible writer\Nstruggled with anxieties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.08,0:13:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah “comforted and soothed” him,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.99,0:13:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,calming his troubled heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.55,0:13:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,God can do the same for us
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.12,0:13:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,through his inspired Word, the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember,\Nthe Bible is how Jehovah speaks to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.16,0:13:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than allowing our emotions to run wild,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.87,0:13:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we can learn to focus\Nour mind on upbuilding things,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.61,0:13:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,such as what\Nthe apostle Paul listed at Philippians 4:8:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.61,0:13:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“Finally, brothers, whatever things are true,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.62,0:13:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are of serious concern,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.75,0:13:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are righteous,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.92,0:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are chaste,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.96,0:14:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are lovable,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.99,0:14:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are well-spoken-of,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.43,0:14:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“whatever things are virtuous,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.76,0:14:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“and whatever things are praiseworthy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.30,0:14:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,continue considering these things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.40,0:14:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The footnote to verse 8 shows that “considering”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.54,0:14:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,involves “thinking about” or “meditating on.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.88,0:14:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We can and should\Nmeditate on positive things from the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,replacing negative things\Nthat may enter our mind and cause anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask Jehovah to help you to find passages
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.19,0:14:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in his Word that will soothe your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.60,0:14:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask others what scriptures have calmed\Ntheir heart during anxious moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.60,0:14:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Make your own personal list.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.47,0:14:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then set aside time to read
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.21,0:14:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and meditate on those passages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.48,0:14:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation is the doorway to your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.68,0:15:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation lets God’s thoughts affect you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.18,0:15:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,on the deepest possible level.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.09,0:15:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that Jehovah is speaking directly to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.79,0:15:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.96,0:15:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Never underestimate the power of God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.56,0:15:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,—of letting Jehovah speak to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.57,0:15:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fourth way to deal with anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.50,0:15:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is to share your feelings with a trusted friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 12:25 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“Anxiety in a man’s heart weighs it down
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.45,0:15:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“[or, as the footnote says, ‘depresses him’],
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.35,0:15:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but a good word cheers it up.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.22,0:15:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“A good word” can come from a fellow believer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.66,0:15:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,who is motivated\Nby God’s spirit and guided by his Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.43,0:15:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When the apostle Paul was alone in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.50,0:15:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he prayed for encouragement
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.97,0:15:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah provided\Nwhat he needed to cheer him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.87,0:15:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With a heart full of appreciation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.48,0:16:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he said at Colossians 4:11
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.88,0:16:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that “my fellow workers  . . . have become
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.31,0:16:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a source of great comfort to me,”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.58,0:16:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or “a strengthening aid.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.12,0:16:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do if you feel\Nweighed down or imprisoned by anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.12,0:16:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Paul, pray for encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.36,0:16:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray for someone you can talk to,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.43,0:16:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,someone you can trust with your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.53,0:16:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer to your prayer may be an elder
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.04,0:16:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or a mature Christian brother or sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.57,0:16:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if it’s difficult for you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.14,0:16:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to open up to others and confide in them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.88,0:16:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Try the advice\Nin the March 1, 1997, Watchtower article
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are You Afraid to Trust Others?”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.25,0:16:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When confiding in someone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.96,0:16:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: “Reveal your concerns gradually.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.53,0:16:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“If he [or she] responds in an appropriate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.53,0:16:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“sympathetic, and discreet way,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.13,0:17:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you might then try disclosing more.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.30,0:17:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it takes some effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.71,0:17:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,never underestimate the power of our brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.74,0:17:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah can use a fellow worshipper
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.35,0:17:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to ease your mind of “anxious concern.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.88,0:17:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Even at times when there’s no one to talk to,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.99,0:17:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we can let the experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.35,0:17:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,upbuilding music,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.79,0:17:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and talks on JW Broadcasting® be like
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.49,0:17:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,an encouraging hug from a trusted friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.76,0:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, when we make the effort,\Nwe give Jehovah something to bless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.77,0:17:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah can help us\Nconquer the seemingly unconquerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.77,0:17:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That may not mean\Nthat we’ll completely eliminate anxiety,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.75,0:17:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can learn to take control.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.75,0:17:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.75,0:17:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember our four ways:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.85,0:17:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,First, rely on Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.02,0:17:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and take one day at time;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.56,0:17:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,second, pour out your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.59,0:18:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah in earnest, specific prayer;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.43,0:18:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,third, read and meditate on God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.24,0:18:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—let Jehovah speak to you;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.14,0:18:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and fourth, share your feelings with a trusted friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.04,0:18:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah’s help,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.08,0:18:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you can deal with anxiety one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.38,0:18:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, I read a quote from the sister who described
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.42,0:18:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,anxiety as a monster living inside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.49,0:18:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so pleased to say that the sister\Nwho wrote that letter about her anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually here with us in the studio\Nto tell us more about her experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.77,0:18:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Jordan Williams\Nand her husband, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.97,0:18:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.10,0:18:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for coming here\Nto share with us your battle with anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.34,0:18:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you elaborate on that, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.24,0:18:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel ashamed of my anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.65,0:18:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like there’s something\Nwrong with me, and I feel guilty about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.28,0:18:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I’m\Nletting Jehovah down by feeling anxious
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.05,0:19:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I’m even being disobedient to Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.72,0:19:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when he says: “Stop being anxious.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.76,0:19:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just can’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.43,0:19:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for sharing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.76,0:19:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Robert, what do you do\Nto help Jordan battle this anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.13,0:19:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a monster\N—sometimes a very stubborn monster—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.24,0:19:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that won’t go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.27,0:19:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Remembering that it’s not her fault
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.68,0:19:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,helps me be more compassionate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.65,0:19:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and caring—listening\Nwhen she’s explaining these anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.35,0:19:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that I may not completely understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.59,0:19:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jordan, are there other\Npractical things that help you battle anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.22,0:19:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The single biggest help\Nis walking with Jehovah every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.49,0:19:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean that literally.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.53,0:19:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll wake up in the morning super anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.13,0:19:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can’t breathe; and my chest is tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.33,0:19:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ll get up, and I’ll read the chapter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.17,0:19:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Bible that the daily text comes from.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.41,0:19:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I’ll go on a walk\Nand talk to Jehovah for an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.04,0:19:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and I try to use\Nthe model prayer as an outline.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.78,0:19:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’ll talk to Jehovah about his name
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.38,0:20:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and how I feel so privileged\Nto have that name on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.15,0:20:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ll talk to him about his Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.49,0:20:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s going to solve\Nall of these problems, including anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.69,0:20:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ll talk to him about his will
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.00,0:20:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and specifically what his will is for me that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.20,0:20:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,those three things\Ncover the things that were worrying me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.34,0:20:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But if there is another thing,\NI’ll talk to him specifically about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.14,0:20:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What a nice walk you have with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.34,0:20:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there other things\Nthat help you deal and battle anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.48,0:20:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal study projects help a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.08,0:20:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,especially if they\Ndon’t have anything to do with anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.32,0:20:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If I do a study project\Non the spiritual suit of armor or the ransom,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.32,0:20:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it kind of distracts the “anxiety monster”\Nso that my heart can calm down,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.70,0:20:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then these pearls of wisdom will\Ncome from Jehovah, and they can get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.60,0:20:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And some of those pearls are actually\Njust what I need to deal with my anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.17,0:20:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there specific things that help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.01,0:21:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I made an Anxiety tab\Nin the Personal Study section
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.64,0:21:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of my Study Bible on my tablet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.85,0:21:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and I collect scriptures and comments
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.38,0:21:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that really help with my anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.42,0:21:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in 2014,\Nthere was a regional convention talk
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.02,0:21:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,about Matthew chapter 6\Nand six specific things that combat anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.03,0:21:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it made me think\Nof the twelve-step program  to overcoming addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.90,0:21:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the six steps to overcome anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.67,0:21:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those six steps?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.37,0:21:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is to help those in need,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.87,0:21:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and then pray a lot, to be forgiving,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.41,0:21:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,not to be hypocritical,\Nto store up treasures in heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.41,0:21:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and then to focus on spiritual matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.22,0:21:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we got back from the convention,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.55,0:21:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,she took those items and she wrote them down
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.72,0:21:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and put them on magnets\Nand put them on our refrigerator.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.29,0:21:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to do each one\Nof those six things every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.53,0:21:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I accomplish one, I’ll turn the magnet
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:21:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I can see what I still need to work on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.27,0:22:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I come\Nto the refrigerator in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.00,0:22:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if the magnets are turned,\Nwe know where she’s at.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If they’re not turned,\Nwe know we’re in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.81,0:22:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a bad day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.81,0:22:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s time to do something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.81,0:22:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good—nice barometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.94,0:22:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what can others do or say
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.24,0:22:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be helpful\Nto those going through anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.11,0:22:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,For the friends,\Nit’s really nice when they’re understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.75,0:22:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and nonjudgmental
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.79,0:22:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and respect my privacy (that’s really helpful)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.46,0:22:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and when they don’t freeze me in time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.09,0:22:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or decide that ‘Oh, she’s anxious,\Nand this is how she’s going to be all the time.’
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.53,0:22:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s really helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.73,0:22:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I even forget that Jehovah approves of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.54,0:22:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So reminding me of that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.64,0:22:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—reminding me that the things\Nthat I do to please him are successful
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.64,0:22:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe even reminding me\Nof things that I have accomplished for Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.58,0:22:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.22,0:22:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you should\Ntell Ron about your broken dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.62,0:22:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.92,0:22:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI’d like to know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.09,0:22:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just found out\Nabout this Japanese art called Kintsukuroi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.29,0:22:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s basically taking
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.29,0:23:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a broken piece of pottery\Nand fixing it by putting it back together
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.97,0:23:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with gold or silver lacquer,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.00,0:23:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the concept is that the piece\Nis more beautiful for having been broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.44,0:23:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And that really resonates\Nwith me because I do feel broken by anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.45,0:23:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah gave Jesus as a ransom,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.75,0:23:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and that ransom is just pure gold;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.98,0:23:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and He can take\Nall the broken anxious little bits of me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.92,0:23:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and put me back together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.96,0:23:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe I’ll even be more\Nuseful to Jehovah for having been broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.53,0:23:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s very precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.23,0:23:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for sharing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.93,0:23:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there other things\Nthat help you deal with anxiety?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.07,0:23:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve learned to recognize\Nwhen anxiety is clouding my thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.50,0:23:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’ll ask him,\N“Can I borrow your brain for a minute, please?”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.81,0:23:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we did is we went\Nand purchased a whiteboard and put it in my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.98,0:23:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes we’ll go to the whiteboard
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.98,0:23:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and write out all\Nthe anxieties that she’s dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.75,0:23:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,As we are writing them out,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.79,0:23:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes we realize that those\Nare yesterday’s anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.55,0:24:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and that they’ve been cared for,\Nso we can erase those from the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.62,0:24:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them are for tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.23,0:24:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we don’t want\Nto borrow those and bring them to today.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.93,0:24:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re tomorrow’s anxieties.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.60,0:24:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And some anxieties\Ncan be grouped in little clusters,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.30,0:24:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can realize,\N‘The root is here; let’s focus on that.’
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.57,0:24:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I fight anxiety every single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.11,0:24:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And anxiety is constantly\Nchanging its tactics, so I have to be adaptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.11,0:24:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah never\Nleaves me to fight anxiety alone—ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.05,0:24:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t understand\Nwhat I’ve done to merit all of his attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.06,0:24:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but I do realize that I don’t\Nneed to understand why he loves me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.96,0:24:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust him, and he never lies,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.63,0:24:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just need to accept it\Nwhen he shows me that love.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.83,0:24:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate\Nyou sharing those personal feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.44,0:24:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, we know\Nthat Jehovah and Jesus are so proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.34,0:24:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that those\Nwho are listening in to this interview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.04,0:24:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will benefit so much\Nfrom listening to your personal expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.45,0:25:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.02,0:25:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Anxieties can surface at any time in our lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.22,0:25:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,even when we’re very young.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.59,0:25:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine, though, if the stress\Nof growing up in this system
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.73,0:25:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,was made worse by a chronic disorder,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.13,0:25:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,one that made anxiety feel impossible to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.63,0:25:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll be encouraged\Nby the experience of Brother Steing Dott,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.47,0:25:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,who never gave up on Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.77,0:25:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,See if you can identify what has helped him cope
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.41,0:25:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.91,0:25:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Steing Dott.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.92,0:25:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born in 1988 in Darwin,\NNorthern Territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.12,0:25:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was eight years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.76,0:25:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that life\Nwas getting very difficult for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.69,0:25:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was diagnosed with ADHD,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.36,0:25:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,obsessive-compulsive disorder,\NTourette syndrome.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.73,0:25:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And on top of all of that,\NI was diagnosed with severe anxiety as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.44,0:25:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My mum said this affected the entire family
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.41,0:26:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because I would repeatedly\Nyell out “Good night!”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.51,0:26:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to each individual person in the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.78,0:26:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And on top of that,\NI used to constantly go
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.18,0:26:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,around the house,\Nchecking the locks and the windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.62,0:26:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My school life was the hardest thing\NI’ve ever had to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.86,0:26:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My school was approximately\N500 meters from my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.70,0:26:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It would take me\Nat least two hours to get to school
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.97,0:26:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because one of my obsessions was\Nthat if there were cracks on the footpath
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.47,0:26:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I stepped on one,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.97,0:26:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d have to go all the way back home\Nand start again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.41,0:26:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I found life\Nto be a constant struggle,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.68,0:26:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and as I got older,\Nit only got worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.42,0:26:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Even at ten years old,\NI decided that I wanted to end my life
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.66,0:26:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it would make\Neveryone in the family’s life a lot easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.63,0:26:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But then we decided\Nto use some medication,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.46,0:26:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which eased my problems a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.67,0:27:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite having medication,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.50,0:27:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,life was still completely unbearable for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.67,0:27:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a constant struggle\Nevery day within myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.21,0:27:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to wash my hands\Nhundreds of times a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.58,0:27:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t leave the home;
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.18,0:27:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t get a driver’s license;\NI couldn’t even get a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.29,0:27:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A major turning point in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.06,0:27:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,was my mum’s unwavering faith in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.06,0:27:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She used to iron\Nmy clothes for the meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.86,0:27:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and hang them on the doorknob,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.66,0:27:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,even though I wasn’t ready\Nto attend the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.13,0:27:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But what she didn’t know\Nwas that when my mum
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.40,0:27:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,went to the meeting with my sister,\NI’d get a Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.54,0:27:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’d try and start to read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.91,0:27:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I also began to pray to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.11,0:27:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one day, I thought,\N‘I’m going to give this a shot.’
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.08,0:27:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I put my suit on, I got ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.92,0:27:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and I went to the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.22,0:27:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went to the Kingdom Hall,\NI was absolutely terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.49,0:27:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.89,0:27:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I got there, I saw an elder
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.73,0:28:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,who used to come and visit me,\Nand he made me feel very relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.30,0:28:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the amazing welcome\Nby the brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.67,0:28:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—it made me feel like I was part\Nof Jehovah’s organization again.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.51,0:28:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture that really helped me
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.67,0:28:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,was 1 Peter 5:7 because it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.91,0:28:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“While you throw all your anxiety on him,\Nbecause he cares for you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.18,0:28:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So this made me feel like\NI had a very powerful Friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.45,0:28:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah wanted me to throw\Nmy anxieties on him because he loved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.26,0:28:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,On September 4, 2010,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.53,0:28:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it was my most important day of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.83,0:28:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized\Nas one of Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.40,0:28:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at Adelaide Entertainment Centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.77,0:28:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I now serve as a ministerial servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.71,0:28:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had the privilege of giving public talks,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.58,0:28:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something I never thought\NI’d ever be able to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.95,0:28:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I completed pioneer school\Nafter three attempts
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.72,0:28:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because the pioneer school\Nenvironment made me feel
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.95,0:29:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,like I was back at school\Nand made me have anxiety again.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.96,0:29:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the third time I completed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.23,0:29:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And none of this would ever have been\Npossible without Jehovah’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.23,0:29:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,On the 6th of August 2016,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.80,0:29:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I married my beautiful wife, Laura,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.04,0:29:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,who helps me serve Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.01,0:29:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can serve\NJehovah every day together.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.74,0:29:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I, like the apostle Paul,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.74,0:29:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,still feel like I have\Na war inside me sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.21,0:29:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But definitely,\NJehovah has never let me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.22,0:29:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Never give up on serving Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.22,0:29:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jehovah\Nwill never give up on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.32,0:29:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice what Steing\Nconsidered the turning point in his life?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.69,0:29:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the unwavering faith of his Mum,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.60,0:29:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the warmth of the congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.10,0:29:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and, most of all, help from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.54,0:29:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He called Jehovah “a very powerful Friend.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.37,0:29:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s so true!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.44,0:29:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Dott overcame monumental challenges,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.31,0:30:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but is his struggle with anxiety over?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.42,0:30:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.12,0:30:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that like the apostle Paul,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.75,0:30:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,he sometimes still feels a war within himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.23,0:30:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you ever feel that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.70,0:30:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s music video reminds us
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.93,0:30:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can find peace and joy despite our burdens.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.90,0:30:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s entitled Each Day Has Its Own Anxieties.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.28,0:30:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I know about the Paradise\Nunder God’s Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.72,0:30:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I believe with all my heart\Nthat better days will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.26,0:30:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes in this life, for me,\NIt’s hard to see the things unseen,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.37,0:31:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To feel the love I know is there\Nwhen my heart is in despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.84,0:31:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know Jehovah’s near.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.92,0:31:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say a prayer from the heart.\NWhen worries overtake my mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.83,0:31:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,On his strength I can rely.\NI’m not alone; I know he’s there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.14,0:31:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I have his words of comfort\NAnd true friends who really care.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.95,0:31:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, each day has its own anxieties.\NSo I take one day at a time;
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.96,0:31:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave tomorrow until tomorrow;\NPeace is what I find
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.53,0:32:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.28,0:32:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So take these words I’ve said, my friend,\NAnd know that I care.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.08,0:32:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on the joys in life,\NNot the burdens that we bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.02,0:32:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about what God has done.\NTo show his love, he gave his Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.06,0:32:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So never doubt; keep trusting him.\NHe gave his best so we could live.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.84,0:32:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So don’t give in to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.24,0:32:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Say a prayer from the heart.\NWhen worries overtake our mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.72,0:33:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,On his strength we can rely.\NWe’re not alone, for he is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.77,0:33:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We have his words of comfort\NAnd true friends who really care.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.94,0:33:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, each day has its own anxieties.\NSo take one day at a time;
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.19,0:33:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave tomorrow until tomorrow;\NPeace is what we’ll find
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.69,0:33:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,One day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.85,0:34:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Say a prayer from the heart.\NWhen worries overtake our mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.66,0:34:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,On his strength we can rely.\NWe’re not alone, for he is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.31,0:34:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We have his words of comfort\NAnd true friends who really care.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.45,0:34:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, each day has its own anxieties.\NSo take one day at a time;
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.12,0:34:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave tomorrow until tomorrow;\NPeace is what we’ll find
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.70,0:34:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One day at a time—\NOne day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.88,0:35:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“We’re not alone, for he is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.42,0:35:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“We have his words of comfort and true friends
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.02,0:35:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,who really care.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.02,0:35:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What an encouraging thought from that song!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.13,0:35:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, true friends who share\Nour love for Jehovah are invaluable.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.17,0:35:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see that in this story from Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.03,0:35:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sisters Takako Sato and Hisako Wakui
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.17,0:35:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,have worked together as pioneers since 1957.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.34,0:35:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s learn how their friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.71,0:35:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,has helped them serve Jehovah with joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.55,0:35:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We are pioneer partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.45,0:35:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve been working together
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.52,0:35:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for over 60 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.02,0:35:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1956,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.66,0:35:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the only Jehovah’s Witness\Nin Nagano prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.90,0:35:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was lonesome,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.10,0:35:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but I applied for regular pioneer service.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.37,0:35:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Surprisingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.61,0:36:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I was appointed\Nas a special pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.14,0:36:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so happy that I found myself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.81,0:36:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,rolling around on the tatami-mat floor
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.82,0:36:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with the appointment letter in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.75,0:36:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the way\NI expressed my joy and appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.16,0:36:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was invited to serve
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.23,0:36:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as a special pioneer,\NI was sent to Nagano,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.76,0:36:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s where I met Hisako.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.03,0:36:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Takako and I focused on our ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.44,0:36:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When an isolated group was established,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.67,0:36:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,since there were no brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.84,0:36:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I would wear a head covering\Nand conduct the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.25,0:36:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the outlines were in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.28,0:36:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn’t understand anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.92,0:36:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But people were delighted to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.32,0:36:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,even just the scriptures and went home satisfied,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.73,0:36:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and that strongly impressed on me\Nthe power of God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.60,0:37:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We were assigned\Nto a territory in the city after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.40,0:37:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We found so many not-at-homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.77,0:37:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but we were determined to meet people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.11,0:37:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we changed the times we preached,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.28,0:37:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and we talked to people on the street
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.48,0:37:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who were going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.29,0:37:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We cherished even small opportunities.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.72,0:37:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When we had a chance to meet a householder,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.93,0:37:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we always tried to have a conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.99,0:37:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that we could link to the next visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.56,0:37:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Before long, I had ten Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.60,0:37:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Takako acts like she’s cheerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.41,0:37:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but she’s been fighting various illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.14,0:37:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, it was so bad
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.91,0:37:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could not even go out in service.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.12,0:37:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a serious skin condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.75,0:37:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not bear
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.16,0:38:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at the illustration of Job in the magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.06,0:38:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and I covered it up with paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.77,0:38:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah helped me\Nto look to Job’s example.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.87,0:38:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.44,0:38:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that our endurance under trial
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.91,0:38:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,would become praise to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.38,0:38:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have often had health problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.85,0:38:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Just at one of those times,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.22,0:38:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I received a letter from the branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.02,0:38:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It said:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.36,0:38:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“What you\Ncan accomplish now may be limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.16,0:38:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“However, think\Nabout all that you have done up to now
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.10,0:38:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“to give praise to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.24,0:38:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“and about the people\Nyou were able to help learn the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.97,0:38:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and be joyful knowing\Nthat you have been used by Jehovah fully.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.55,0:38:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t stop crying
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.58,0:39:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because I really felt the care and concern
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.22,0:39:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,from the organization and from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.73,0:39:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hisako also\Ntook really good care of me
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.20,0:39:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and prayed with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.20,0:39:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our thinking and personalities are different,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.47,0:39:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but we made efforts to talk things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.44,0:39:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Our heartfelt desire\Nto want to serve Jehovah full-time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.38,0:39:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,has always been the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.12,0:39:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,For 60 years, we’ve enjoyed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.19,0:39:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a truly wonderful life of service to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.72,0:39:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has supported us in difficult times
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.73,0:39:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,through the Bible, the organization, and friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.10,0:39:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I have tasted the truthfulness of the words:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.80,0:39:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“When I am weak, then I am powerful.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.61,0:39:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‘When I said: “My foot is slipping,”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.31,0:40:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,your kindness, O Jehovah, has supported me.’
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.18,0:40:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I can say that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.75,0:40:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we don’t have energy or ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.09,0:40:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve been able to enjoy\Nfull-time service together up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.30,0:40:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m really content now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.23,0:40:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all thanks to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.37,0:40:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the apostle Paul,\Nour sisters cultivated singleness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.61,0:40:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and focused on full-time service to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.01,0:40:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,for more than 60 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.45,0:40:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they face everyday challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.35,0:40:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the extra ones that come with age,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.12,0:40:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but their heartfelt desire\Nto serve Jehovah whole-souled
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.36,0:40:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,brings Takako and Hisako\Nreal joy and contentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.00,0:40:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole-souled service\Nfor nearly 20,000 brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.60,0:40:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is a full-time assignment at Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.10,0:41:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What motivates them\Nto reach out for this special privilege?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.68,0:41:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What blessings do they experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.35,0:41:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And what’s the best way\Nto prepare and qualify for Bethel service?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.18,0:41:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to invite my friend Patrick LaFranca
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.25,0:41:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to discuss these and other questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.59,0:41:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, Pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.99,0:41:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.83,0:41:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How heartwarming it’s been
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.33,0:41:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to see millions take their stand for true worship!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.96,0:41:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands more are joining us every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.54,0:41:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is speeding up the ingathering work,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.97,0:41:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and this makes us very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.91,0:41:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But who will work\Nto provide the Bibles, Bible literature,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.58,0:41:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and the audio and video publications
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.02,0:41:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that sustain us spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.08,0:41:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and help us to accomplish\Nour Kingdom preaching and teaching work?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.72,0:41:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Bethel is a unique place.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.86,0:41:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s where mature Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.23,0:41:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,render sacred service to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.63,0:41:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in close association with Christ’s brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.00,0:42:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They minister to the needs\Nof our worldwide brotherhood
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.87,0:42:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and support the preaching work.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.67,0:42:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bethel family is a group of dedicated,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.64,0:42:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,baptized servants of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.81,0:42:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,who live and work together closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.78,0:42:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So they experience in a special way
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.29,0:42:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what Psalm 133:1 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.56,0:42:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look! How good
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.33,0:42:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“and how pleasant it is for brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.03,0:42:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to dwell together in unity!”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.43,0:42:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re very pleased to see\Nthat many have expanded their service
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.50,0:42:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah by making themselves available
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.97,0:42:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for the special privilege of Bethel service.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.27,0:42:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you considered this as a goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.61,0:42:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Making yourself available
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.61,0:42:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,for Bethel service\Nis like knocking on a door that leads
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.02,0:42:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to many other privileges of service.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.92,0:42:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, to serve at Bethel requires
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.42,0:42:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a self-sacrificing spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.66,0:42:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and a willingness to serve
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.49,0:43:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever there is a need,\Nin harmony with the attitude displayed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.26,0:43:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,by the prophet Isaiah at Isaiah 6:8:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.43,0:43:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then I heard the voice of Jehovah saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.34,0:43:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Whom shall I send, and who will go for us?’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.91,0:43:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said: ‘Here I am! Send me!’”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.91,0:43:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When Isaiah learned about an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.72,0:43:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to do more in Jehovah’s service,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.72,0:43:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he responded eagerly,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.72,0:43:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,even though he did not know exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.89,0:43:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what he was going to be assigned to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.36,0:43:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It was enough for him to know that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.43,0:43:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,was extending an invitation\Nto serve in a special way,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.36,0:43:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and Isaiah wanted to volunteer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.43,0:43:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The same spirit is shown\Nby Bethel family members worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.44,0:43:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What especially motivates\Nso many to serve at Bethel?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.44,0:43:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Love for Jehovah moves us
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.81,0:43:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to put Kingdom interests ahead of self-interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.82,0:43:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As stated in the Proclaimers book, page 295:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.65,0:44:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is not work in which they gain
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.32,0:44:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“personal prominence or material possessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.33,0:44:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Their desire is to honor Jehovah,\Nand they are satisfied
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.83,0:44:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the provisions made for them
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.06,0:44:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the way of food, lodging,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.97,0:44:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and a modest [allowance]\Nfor personal expenses.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.04,0:44:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any rewards\Nthat come from serving in this unique way?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.57,0:44:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have offered themselves willingly
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.04,0:44:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,for Bethel service have truly been blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.75,0:44:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The love and unity we feel here is incomparable.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.72,0:44:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not like in a company out in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.15,0:44:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because here you can work\Nwith your friends every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.43,0:44:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Like-minded people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.20,0:44:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,have the same goals and support each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.53,0:44:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what you can feel here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.03,0:44:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’re assigned a task
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.74,0:44:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’ve never performed before,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.10,0:44:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but there are\Nmany experienced brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.47,0:44:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,who can help\N—professionally as well as personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.68,0:45:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it is the consideration of the daily text
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.78,0:45:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or the Watchtower Study with the Bethel family,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.78,0:45:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,listening to the practical, valuable comments
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.05,0:45:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of our brothers and sisters is really refreshing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.52,0:45:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You really feel that they love Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.36,0:45:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and their comments help you to feel the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.40,0:45:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in Bethel, you have the best Employer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.46,0:45:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is—Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.47,0:45:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No other employer\Nis as grateful and considerate as he is,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.24,0:45:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so out of love for Jehovah,\Nyou’re simply happy to give him your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.94,0:45:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever I think about what
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.44,0:45:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is being done at Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.08,0:45:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—publications are being
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.45,0:45:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,produced and shipped,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.58,0:45:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,videos for our conventions are being made,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.18,0:45:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and translation is being done
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.45,0:45:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,into so many different languages—
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.72,0:45:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep getting goose bumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.26,0:45:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what I can do here,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.26,0:45:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that by doing it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.39,0:45:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I am supporting Christ’s brothers\Nmakes me feel very, very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.13,0:45:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does a young person
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.13,0:45:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,qualify for Bethel service?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.87,0:45:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents raised me to have
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.14,0:46:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.77,0:46:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So during the school holidays
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.78,0:46:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and growing up,\Nour life revolved around the ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.75,0:46:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—doing spiritual activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.75,0:46:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And it really helped us
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.95,0:46:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,keep focused spiritually as a family
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.99,0:46:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and helped me stay focused\Non the goals that I wanted to achieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.66,0:46:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I really enjoy reading,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.59,0:46:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and one day my Dad just said to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.33,0:46:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why don’t you read the Bible?”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.87,0:46:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know it sounds obvious,\Nbut at that point, I had never read it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.17,0:46:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from Genesis to Revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.64,0:46:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I finished reading the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.64,0:46:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it really changed my thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.24,0:46:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and it really proved the truth to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.21,0:46:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And this helped me to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.32,0:46:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual focus, and it really was the first step
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.86,0:46:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in reaching out and achieving
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.86,0:46:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual goals that I wanted to achieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.03,0:46:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In the congregation, I was able to help out
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.96,0:46:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with doing the magazines\Nand the sound and the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.03,0:47:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And these privileges really helped me to build
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.80,0:47:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a good work ethic and give in ways
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.81,0:47:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could give more to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.81,0:47:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the elders used to work\Nwith me a lot in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.81,0:47:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I felt
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.98,0:47:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘I can’t do this’
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.98,0:47:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or ‘This is too much’ or ‘It’s too overwhelming’
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.98,0:47:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,or ‘I’ll never be able to reach this goal,’\Nan elder showed me
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.05,0:47:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a scripture in the Bible where Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.96,0:47:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,was encouraging Joshua to be courageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.89,0:47:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And that really impacted me,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.90,0:47:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I was able to be courageous,\Ntoo, and to reach my goal of Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.50,0:47:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I visited Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.51,0:47:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw that they were normal people,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.44,0:47:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and they had so many good qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.88,0:47:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wanted to imitate
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.11,0:47:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—very hospitable, very warm,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.18,0:47:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,very inviting.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.29,0:47:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That helped me to want to reach my goal,\Nso that I could be like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.39,0:47:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To serve at Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.23,0:48:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,there are qualifications that need to be met.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.43,0:48:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have a deep love for Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.97,0:48:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the organization, which is demonstrated
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.67,0:48:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,by living in harmony with Bible standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.44,0:48:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You must have a fine reputation
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.91,0:48:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as a spiritual person.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.91,0:48:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have respect
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.94,0:48:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s moral standards,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.95,0:48:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,avoiding uncleanness and sexual immorality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.98,0:48:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have a clean conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.05,0:48:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,before Jehovah and be at peace with yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.02,0:48:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and with Jehovah’s organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.09,0:48:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dress and grooming should be exemplary,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.99,0:48:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,befitting a Christian minister
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.10,0:48:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,even during leisure time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.23,0:48:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Styles that are faddish
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.23,0:48:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or extreme or that identify us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.94,0:48:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with undesirable elements of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.44,0:48:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are not acceptable at Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.91,0:48:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The applicant should not read, listen to,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.61,0:48:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or view any type of material
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.01,0:48:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that is inappropriate for a Christian.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.28,0:48:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Such unwholesome material
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.42,0:48:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly would include pornography,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.72,0:49:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,debasing music, or any kind of entertainment
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.32,0:49:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that features sexual immorality,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.66,0:49:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritism, or violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.16,0:49:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Bethel applicants should be
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.16,0:49:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from 19 to 35 years of age.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.07,0:49:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally, there is an opening
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.30,0:49:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for someone over 35 years of age
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.57,0:49:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who may have specialized skills
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.57,0:49:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that are needed at Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.58,0:49:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,such as those with certain technical
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.58,0:49:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or medical experience, translation skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.81,0:49:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or building trades such as plumbing, electrical,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.82,0:49:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,heavy equipment mechanics, or carpentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.29,0:49:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Those with such capabilities and training
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.92,0:49:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are welcome to apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.99,0:49:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In view of the unique demands
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.06,0:49:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of a full-time assignment at Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.20,0:49:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you should be mentally and emotionally sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.67,0:49:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,physically strong, and able to work long hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.14,0:49:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be able to read, write,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.98,0:49:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and speak the primary language
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.98,0:49:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of the branch territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.98,0:50:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This will enable you to communicate well
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.15,0:50:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with others serving at Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.15,0:50:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to receive needed training, and to work safely
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.19,0:50:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bethel environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.06,0:50:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Bethel applicants agree to serve
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.06,0:50:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for a minimum of one year,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.06,0:50:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,during which time you will receive training
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.46,0:50:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for continued Bethel service.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.03,0:50:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,With regard to secular skills,\Nwe do not encourage individuals
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.54,0:50:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to obtain university education
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.54,0:50:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or training with the thought that this will improve
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.11,0:50:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,their chances of being called into Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.71,0:50:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The best way to prepare for Bethel service
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.81,0:50:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is to first serve in the full-time pioneer ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.75,0:50:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest need is for single brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.56,0:50:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,However, all who meet\Nthe qualifications, including sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.96,0:50:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,are encouraged to apply\Nfor temporary volunteer service.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.23,0:50:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Serving as\Na temporary volunteer at Bethel may open
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.13,0:50:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to other opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.13,0:50:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to expand your service to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.40,0:51:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are interested\Nin applying for Bethel service,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.27,0:51:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,which application should you request
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.38,0:51:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from a member\Nof your Congregation Service Committee?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.81,0:51:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Since there are two types
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.81,0:51:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of applications available, first give careful
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.75,0:51:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and prayerful consideration
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.75,0:51:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to your circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.76,0:51:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereafter, decide whether\Nyou will request from the elders
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.83,0:51:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the Application for Volunteer Program (A-19),
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.06,0:51:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which is available for those interested
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.83,0:51:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in serving on a temporary basis
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.00,0:51:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for as brief as one week or as long
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.24,0:51:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as several consecutive months.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.37,0:51:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you may decide to request
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.74,0:51:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the Application to Become\Na Member of the Worldwide Order
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.68,0:51:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of Special Full-Time Servants\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses (A-8).
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.05,0:51:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This application is for those interested
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.82,0:51:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in serving on a long-term basis
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.99,0:51:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for one full year or longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.45,0:51:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Branch Committee\Ndetermines that there is a need
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.59,0:51:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,for your services, they will decide
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.66,0:51:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can best be used, whether at Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.70,0:51:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,or perhaps on\Na theocratic construction assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.97,0:52:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Submitting your application may open
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.47,0:52:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a door of opportunity to serve Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.50,0:52:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and his organization in a variety of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.44,0:52:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, not all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.95,0:52:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,who have such a self-sacrificing spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.28,0:52:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,have the circumstances in life to serve at Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.15,0:52:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can encourage others who do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.42,0:52:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents, follow the example
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.36,0:52:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of God-fearing parents
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.56,0:52:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Hannah and Elkanah,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.26,0:52:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who willingly made their son available
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.90,0:52:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for expanded theocratic privileges.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.00,0:52:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue to place the goal\Nof Bethel service before your young ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.71,0:52:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and stimulate\Ntheir interest in the full-time ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.21,0:52:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,by your example and your positive expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.58,0:52:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.59,0:52:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,bring them on tour\Nof world headquarters in New York, U.S.A.,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.99,0:53:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or make arrangements\Nto bring them on a tour of the Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.09,0:53:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in the branch territory in which you live.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.56,0:53:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Such visits can help\Nyoung ones to witness firsthand
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.70,0:53:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the work that’s being done\Nat Bethel to promote Kingdom interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.37,0:53:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Elders, help young ones in your congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.44,0:53:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,who have the potential to expand their service
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.81,0:53:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah to meet the qualifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.48,0:53:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah continues to look\Nfor those willing to respond
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.59,0:53:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to his invitation to expand their service to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.86,0:53:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As in Isaiah’s day, He asks:
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.63,0:53:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whom shall I send, and who will go for us?”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.53,0:53:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you answer as did the prophet:
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.67,0:53:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“Here I am! Send me!”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.47,0:53:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We encourage you to progress to spiritual maturity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.27,0:53:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and serve Jehovah whole-souled.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.68,0:53:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In due time, you may qualify to serve at Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.45,0:53:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or in another form of exciting theocratic service
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.28,0:54:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that permits you to use the health and strength
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.09,0:54:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah has granted you in an expanded way,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.59,0:54:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,all to his praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.09,0:54:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be assured that we love you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.96,0:54:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for the willing spirit you show
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.07,0:54:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as you continue to reach out in Jehovah’s service.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.14,0:54:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.17,0:54:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope\Nthat the information Brother LaFranca shared
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.91,0:54:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,motivates many more to have
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.01,0:54:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the prophet Isaiah’s willing and self-sacrificing spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.28,0:54:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So much of what Jehovah provides encourages us
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.05,0:54:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep busy with spiritual things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.76,0:54:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For one,\Nwe’re looking forward to our upcoming conventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.93,0:54:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme for this year is “‘Love Never Fails’!”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.33,0:54:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like a preview of the program?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.10,0:54:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.10,0:54:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Love
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.71,0:54:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,—is it gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.98,0:54:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Have we lost it?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.85,0:55:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the possession of the wealthy?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.25,0:55:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the strong?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.32,0:55:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.66,0:55:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At the 2019 convention of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.63,0:55:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you will learn what real love is,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.63,0:55:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,where to find it,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.33,0:55:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and how to show it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.97,0:55:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and have it shown in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.21,0:55:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,God cares deeply about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.31,0:55:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wants you to know
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.44,0:55:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that in this hate-filled world,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.81,0:55:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,love can be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.35,0:55:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.79,0:55:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And that love will never fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.23,0:55:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ve discussed,\Nwe should never underestimate the power
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.40,0:55:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of our brotherhood\Nto help us overcome worries and anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.80,0:56:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Our conventions are wonderful opportunities\Nfor us to encourage one another
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.24,0:56:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by the hundreds,\Nthousands, and tens of thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.85,0:56:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And this year, we’re especially excited
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.92,0:56:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that 24 international conventions
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.82,0:56:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will be held throughout the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.12,0:56:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Use the opportunity\Nto get to know more of your brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.13,0:56:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at the regional\Nor international convention you attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.03,0:56:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To conclude this month’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.57,0:56:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s visit our brothers in Turkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.30,0:56:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Turkey is a nation of more than 80 million people
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.67,0:56:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and a land rich in Bible history.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.25,0:56:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Turkey occupies a unique geographic position,\Nbridging Europe and Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.55,0:56:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s here that Noah’s ark\Ncame to rest near Mount Ararat,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.26,0:56:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Turkey’s highest mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.76,0:56:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the land\Nof the congregations in Colossae and Galatia,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.26,0:56:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as all seven congregations
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.60,0:57:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned in Revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.90,0:57:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The territory is diverse and vast,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.07,0:57:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with a publisher-to-population ratio
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.04,0:57:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of 1 to more than 26,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.01,0:57:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In the capital city of Ankara,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.05,0:57:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a single congregation is working hard
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.35,0:57:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach almost 5.5 million people.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.65,0:57:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Many congregations in Turkey\Nfocus on public witnessing, with encouraging results.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.73,0:57:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s visit the Hatay Congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.26,0:57:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,near the ancient city of Syrian Antioch.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.70,0:57:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul used Antioch\Nas his home base for his missionary tours.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.54,0:57:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was here\Nthat the disciples were first called Christians.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.54,0:57:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Today,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.08,0:57:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this part of Turkey is known for its food
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.78,0:57:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—such as spices, herbs, fruits, and sweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.82,0:57:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In recent times,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.82,0:57:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,unrest and war have disrupted the region.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.63,0:58:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of our brothers and sisters\Nhave been so near to the conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.10,0:58:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that they could hear\Nexplosions from bombs and gunfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.87,0:58:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite these threats and anxieties,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.24,0:58:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the 56 publishers, including 11 regular pioneers
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.18,0:58:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and 2 special pioneers, attend the meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.15,0:58:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and preach without letup.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.08,0:58:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters\Nin Turkey send their love and greetings
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.52,0:58:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to the worldwide brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.72,0:58:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Our love goes back to them\Nfor their zeal and steadfast faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.63,0:58:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.83,0:58:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.
